This software is designed to integrate with healthcare systems and may process
Protected Health Information (PHI) and other sensitive healthcare data. Users
of this software are responsible for:

1. Ensuring compliance with all applicable healthcare regulations, including
   but not limited to HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability
   Act), HITECH (Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical
   Health Act), and other relevant local, state, and federal regulations.

2. Implementing appropriate technical, physical, and administrative safeguards
   to protect the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of healthcare
   data processed through this software.

3. Obtaining all necessary Business Associate Agreements (BAAs) and other
   required legal agreements with athenahealth and other third parties.

4. Conducting appropriate security assessments, risk analyses, and compliance
   audits before deploying this software in production environments.

5. Maintaining comprehensive audit logs and documentation as required by
   applicable regulations.

THE AUTHORS AND CONTRIBUTORS OF THIS SOFTWARE MAKE NO REPRESENTATIONS OR
WARRANTIES REGARDING HIPAA COMPLIANCE, REGULATORY COMPLIANCE, OR FITNESS FOR
USE IN HEALTHCARE ENVIRONMENTS. USE OF THIS SOFTWARE IN PRODUCTION HEALTHCARE
SETTINGS IS AT YOUR OWN RISK.

Users must independently verify that their implementation meets all applicable
